Package: lexiExpand
Title: Semantic Dictionary Expander for Text Analysis
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Gopi Nath", "Vajpai",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "gvajpai@udel.edu")
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Description: Expands seed dictionaries used in dictionary-based text analysis
    by finding semantically similar words using pre-trained GloVe word
    embeddings. Given a small set of seed words (e.g. c("sad", "angry")),
    the package computes cosine similarity across a large vocabulary and
    returns a ranked list of candidates. Supports two multi-seed strategies:
    per-seed neighbor search (preserves which seed drove each match) and
    centroid mode (finds words nearest the averaged semantic center of all
    seeds jointly). An interactive review wizard lets researchers accept or
    reject candidates word-by-word. Accepted words can be exported to plain
    lists, data frames, or 'quanteda' dictionary objects. Vectors are
    downloaded once via Stanford NLP or the 'textdata' package and cached
    locally; no API key is required, ensuring full reproducibility.
